            <title>[LU-13906] Build make use of %{name} consistent</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13906</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;rpmbuild when specifying the lustre_name: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    rpmbuild --define &quot;lustre_name lustre_ib&quot; lustre.spec&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Results in an inconsistent build where package names and dependencies do not align.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example depending on lustre-osd... (where the built package is lustre_ib-osd...)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
